I do like this (pardon me) watering hole in the wall for a number of reasons. Firstly, theres a lot of art and desiderata over the majority of the interior, and secondly, the place is very intimate and hardly ever banging (i confess I dont go there at night too often, because why would I?), and Thirdly, its got a great customer area out back, with pretty cool/chill people, lots of succulents and, even though its not a huge space, it does offer nice spread out seating and plenty of elbow room for those of us in need of such stuff. Oh, I almost forgot: the barkeeps make good drinks, are no-nonsense, generally very chill, earnest and friendly, it all adds up to more than the sum of its parts. Id rate it higher but thats a tall order, probably an interior update, floors and all (including the stage, bathrooms and outside - maybe I missed it but a music on demand system and wifi thats accessible would be transformative and probably make it my goto for a simple place to go where everybody knows your name), and it honestly wouldnt take much. At any rate, Cheers!

ReviewContent: A good dive bar for local music. The drinks are reasonable, I dont think theyre overpriced. The music can be hit or miss, so its good to check out the lineup and see if the bands have a website with music. The staff was friendly and the service was decent. A little bit of sound absorption on the ceiling and walls would be a huge help at this venue. Some of the bands can be too loud, so bring ear plugs just in case. Parking is a bit tough to find, so carpool with your friends. Got a chill patio in the back that is a nice place to chill between bands and get a bit of fresh air. Overall, Id say this is a great spot that needs to get a little bit more support. Music venues seem to be disappearing and this one tends to have some decent shows, so go out and listen to some music.
